SIMPLE: ergot
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ergot
<hw>Er"got</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>ergot</ets>,
<ets>argot</ets>, lit., a spur.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A diseased
condition of rye and other cereals, in which the grains become black,
and often spur-shaped. It is caused by a parasitic fungus,
<spn>Claviceps purpurea</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The mycelium or spawn of this fungus infecting
grains of rye and wheat. It is a powerful remedial agent, and also a
dangerous poison, and is used as a means of hastening childbirth, and to
arrest bleeding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A stub, like soft horn, about the
size of a chestnut, situated behind and below the pastern
joint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>See 2d <er>Calcar</er>, 3
<sd>(b)</sd>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ergotic</ent>⟦br⟧
